source "https://rubygems.org"

gem "github-pages", group: :jekyll_plugins
gem "jekyll-remote-theme"
gem "jekyll-feed"
```

---

### 4. Check your GitHub Actions workflow

Look at `.github/workflows/` in your Blog repo — it likely has a Pages deploy workflow. Make sure it has `jekyll-remote-theme` support. The default `github-pages` workflow handles this automatically, so you should be fine.

---

### 5. Add posts

Create a `_posts/` folder and add posts using the standard Jekyll naming convention:
```
_posts/2026-03-22-my-first-post.md
